      • setCellSize

        public SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions setCellSize(int cellSize)
        Sets the grid cell size used for indexing, in pixels. Larger cells result in faster rendering speed, but worse fidelity. Default is 10 pixels, for large datasets (>10k points), use 15.
        Parameters:
        cellSize - The cell size in pixels.
        Returns:
        The updated SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions

      • setAlgorithm

        public SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions setAlgorithm(SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions.RenderingAlgorithm algorithm)
        Sets the rendering algorithm. There are three options: NO_OPTIMIZATION: Slowest option. Draw all points on each draw event. MEDIUM_OPTIMIZATION: Faster. Recalculates the grid index on each draw event. Not recommended for >10k points. Better UX, but may be choppier. MAXIMUM_OPTIMIZATION: Fastest. Only recalculates the grid on touch up and animation end , hence much faster display on move. Recommended for >10k points.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - A SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions.RenderingAlgorithm.
        Returns:
        The updated SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions

      • setMinZoomShowLabels

        public SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions setMinZoomShowLabels(int minZoomShowLabels)
        Sets the minimum zoom level at which the labels should be drawn. This option is ignored if LabelPolicy is DENSITY_THRESHOLD.
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • setMaxNShownLabels

        public SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions setMaxNShownLabels(int maxNShownLabels)
        Sets the threshold (nr. of visible points) after which labels will not be drawn. This option only works when LabelPolicy is DENSITY_THRESHOLD and the algorithm is MAXIMUM_OPTIMIZATION.
        Parameters:
        maxNShownLabels - The maximum number of visible points
        Returns:

      • setLabelPolicy

        public SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions setLabelPolicy(SimpleFastPointOverlayOptions.LabelPolicy labelPolicy)
        Sets the policy for displaying point labels. Can be:
        ZOOM_THRESHOLD: Labels are not displayed is current map zoom level is lower than MinZoomShowLabels DENSITY_THRESHOLD: Labels are not displayed when the number of visible points is larger than MaxNShownLabels. This only works for MAXIMUM_OPTIMIZATION
        Parameters:
        labelPolicy - One of ZOOM_THRESHOLD or DENSITY_THRESHOLD
        Returns:
